   {:e #blake3 "7e398414d801cb8392902ece6e04d5ff63115ced7d8027097d7c5a78069862eb" :a :adr/decision :v "The daemon reuses the exact JSON-RPC protocol and tool dispatch from mcp.rs. The daemon IS the MCP server with a different transport (Unix socket instead of stdio). This means daemon.rs is a thin wrapper that: (1) manages lifecycle (start/stop/lock), (2) accepts connections on Unix socket, (3) delegates to the same handle_tools_call functions from mcp.rs." :op :assert}
